data.title: Al fresco winner
data.text: A good place on a warm summer day for drinks and bites on the sidewalk tables. Our group enjoyed several hours of leisurely sipping and snacking on a weekday after work. The deli offered up meatballs and a variety of other shareable items from their eclectic menu, and each member of our group selected their beverage from a wide list of hard and soft items. Don't bring your car, parking is difficult. Limited indoor seating, so not as optimal on cold or wet days.

data.title: Eclectic
data.text: This place offers a lot of choices: they have cheeses and meats from Europe, you can always order a custom made sandwich from that selection, or buy some already prepared food. Try jamon from Spain, ir their vegetable gazpacho! it is delicious!

data.title: Convinient and Fast
data.text: Whenever I am looking for a quick lunch, I go to Babo. They have a variety of options and I have noticed these change depending on the day. It's fairly pricy though, so beware.

data.title: Cool urban spot  but....
data.text:
We were on our way to GR and decided to have a little bite there. Place is cool, airy,food  was tasty but overall is pricy for what you get. Self service , plastic utensils, plastic plates,trays...it seems like a buffet style. 
I would reconsider for next time.

data.title: A beautiful urban delicatessen.
data.text: They have achieved a top of the line establishment in down town Ann Arbor that has a balanced feel of old and new world ambience. The seating may be a challenge since it is a very popular place and the staff is one of the friendliest ever encountered. Beautiful ready made subs and sides and a booming carry out business. Park where you can if you are travelling by car. Easy to find as it is on a corner.

data.title: I'd go here for lunch if i lived in Ann Arbor.
data.text: Pleasant and airy, with a really nice selection of craft beers and foodie-type salads.  Excellent spot for lunch, whether eat-in or take-out.

data.title: Terrific food!
data.text: Terrific food, well trained and personable staff and a super clean store...what else do you want? This is a wonderful small market that offers really tasty food (Four cheese Mac and Cheese, pulled pork and marinated chicken parts were all very good choice).

data.title: Grocery with a cafe, or cafe with a grocery?  Go and enjoy anyway.
data.text:
I stopped in to get some snacks and other things, as we were renting a house nearby for a family get- together.  There are many food items here, some carry- out / ready to eat, some normal (take home and prepare yourself) and some eat- in, all very high- standard.  
The fellow who seemed to be running the place (Peter) is easy to talk to and also made some other good recommendations in the area.
They have a lot of authentic Italian salamis and even Spanish Jamon Iberico.  There are fresh- baked croissants, excellent crafted coffees and in the afternoons, a nice selection of brews on draft which you can enjoy at the tables outside or at the counter seating inside.  The sandwiches are on fantastic bread and with the deli counter ingredients are small works of art.  Certainly not fancy dining, but great for an informal brunch or a lunch.
